## Domains

:::domains
wave.site (build mode — website builder)
doc.surf (plan mode — team docs & tasks)
surf.new (public landing & signup)
:::

Subdomain routing handled by middleware — requests routed by `Host` header to the appropriate mode.

## CI/CD

:::cicd[provider=github-actions]
tests: cargo test --workspace
migration_check: sequential numbering, no empty files, no gaps
rust_toolchain: 1.89
cache: swatinem/rust-cache@v2
flyctl: superfly/flyctl-actions v1.5
deploy_timeout: 300s
auto_rollback: true (staging + production)
:::

### Smoke Tests

:::smoke[script=scripts/smoke-test.sh]
GET /healthz -> 200
GET /login -> 200
GET /signup -> 200
GET /access -> 200
GET /privacy -> 308
GET /terms -> 308
GET /dashboard -> 303
GET /account -> 303
GET /billing -> 303
GET /api/auth/.well-known/jwks.json -> 200
GET /nonexistent-page-that-should-404 -> 404
:::

### Deploy Targets

:::deploy_urls
develop: https://surf-app-develop.fly.dev
staging: https://surf-app-staging.fly.dev
production: https://surf-app.fly.dev
:::

## Shared Crates

:::crates
cloudsurf-auth (github: cloudsurf-software/cloudsurf-auth, branch: main)
cloudsurf-db (github: cloudsurf-software/cloudsurf-db, branch: main)
cloudsurf-rate-limiter (github: cloudsurf-software/cloudsurf-rate-limiter, branch: main)
cloudsurf-llm (features: sqlx, stream)
surf-parse (features: pdf)
:::

## Rate Limits

:::data[format=table id=rate-limits]
Limiter | Limit/Hour | Purpose
rate_limiter | 60 | General requests
auth_rate_limiter | 10 | Auth attempts
api_rate_limiter | 60 | API calls
contact_rate_limiter | 5 | Contact form
publish_rate_limiter | 5 | Site publishes
support_rate_limiter | 10 | Support requests
subscribe_rate_limiter | 10 | Email subscriptions
visitor_chat_rate_limiter | 20 | Visitor chat
ads_rate_limiter | 30 | Ads operations
:::

## Auth Methods

:::data[format=table id=auth-methods]
Method | Crate/Service | Purpose
OPAQUE (RFC 9807) | cloudsurf-auth | Password authentication
Ed25519 JWT | cloudsurf-auth (jsonwebtoken) | API token auth
Session cookies | tower-sessions + PostgreSQL store | Browser session auth
Phone/SMS | Twilio Verify | Phone verification (optional)
Turnstile | Cloudflare | Bot protection (optional)
:::

## External Integrations

:::data[format=table id=integrations]
Service | Purpose | Required
Stripe | Subscription billing & webhooks | Recommended
AWS SES | Transactional email | Recommended
Cloudflare | Turnstile CAPTCHA + DNS | Recommended
OpenSRS | Domain registration | Optional
Twilio | Phone verification | Optional
Google Ads | Ad campaign management | Optional
GitHub | App integration (webhooks) | Optional
:::

## Architecture Decisions

::decision[status=accepted date="2026-02-25" deciders="Brady"]
### Unified Application

Merged Build Mode (wavesite) and Plan Mode (tasksurf) into a single binary.
Reduces operational overhead from 2 apps to 1. Subdomain routing separates
the modes at the HTTP layer without separate deployments.
::

::decision[status=accepted date="2026-02-22" deciders="Brady"]
### Shared Auth Database

Single `cloudsurf-auth-db` PostgreSQL instance shared across all products.
User accounts created once, synced to product databases on first access.
Avoids credential duplication and enables single sign-on across wave.site,
doc.surf, and future products.
::

::decision[status=accepted date="2026-02-27" deciders="Brady"]
### Single Region (sjc)

All Fly.io machines in San Jose. Multi-region adds latency complexity
(read replicas, write forwarding) that isn't justified at current scale.
Revisit when p95 latency from non-US users becomes a growth bottleneck.
::

::decision[status=accepted date="2026-02-23" deciders="Brady"]
### No Direct DDL

All schema changes ONLY through git-committed migration files deployed via
CI/CD pipeline. Never run DDL via `flyctl ssh` + `psql`. Learned from
02/23 outage where a manual ALTER TABLE caused migration drift.
::

::

